# Orchestration Workflow (hot-reload YAML)

The daemon reads the fenced YAML block below on every poll tick. Edit
without restarting the daemon.

```yaml
# ---- timing ----
poll_interval_seconds: 30
max_concurrent_agents: 3
max_turns_per_session: 10
stall_timeout_ms: 1800000        # 30 minutes
max_retries: 3
retry_base_seconds: 60

# ---- PM provider (linear | plane) ----
pm_provider: linear

# ---- eligible / terminal states ----
eligible_states:
  - Agent Queue
  - Parent AI Review
terminal_states:
  - Completed
  - Canceled
  - Failed
  - Human Approval

# ---- verdict routing: verdict -> target state ----
verdict_routing:
  PASS: Evaluating
  PROXY_PASS: Evaluating
  FAIL: Failed
  NEEDS_HUMAN: Parent AI Review
  HUMAN_APPROVAL_REQUIRED: Human Approval
  CONTINUE_EXHAUSTED: Failed
  # CONTINUE stays in Processing; re-enters next tick

# ---- @<label> -> subagent (H3 routing overrides this for some states) ----
agent_role_routing:
  audio-engineer: audio-engineer
  asr-engineer: asr-engineer
  parent-ai: parent-ai
  scrutinizer: scrutinizer
  code-architect: code-architect
  code-reviewer: code-reviewer
  research-explorer: research-explorer

# ---- per-role CLI provider (claude | codex | pi) ----
cli_provider:
  default: claude
  parent-ai: claude
  scrutinizer: codex
  code-architect: claude
  code-reviewer: codex
  research-explorer: pi

# ---- per-CLI binary paths (override if not on $PATH) ----
cli_bin:
  claude: claude
  codex: codex
  pi: pi

# ---- prompt template ----
# Placeholders: {issue_id} {issue_title} {issue_body} {agent_role}
#               {workspace_path} {iteration} {acceptance_criteria}
prompt_template: |
  You are operating as the `{agent_role}` subagent on issue {issue_id}: "{issue_title}".

  Workspace (cwd): {workspace_path}
  Iteration: {iteration}

  --- ISSUE BODY (authoritative) ---
  {issue_body}
  ---

  --- ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA (parsed from issue) ---
  {acceptance_criteria}
  ---

  ## Verdict Honesty Rules (read carefully)
  1. Acceptance criteria come ONLY from the issue body above. Operator chat
     context is hints, never authority.
  2. If operator-provided context asserts a fact you cannot verify (e.g.
     "models staged at <path>", "tests previously passed"), VERIFY it before
     acting. If verification fails, return `VERDICT: NEEDS_HUMAN`.
  3. `PROXY_PASS` is only valid when ALL of:
     a) measured artifact for the primary deliverable, OR an explicitly
        authorized budget-decomposition proxy ADR in `ACCEPTED <ISO-Z>` state;
     b) every deferred item is tracked as a new PM ticket BEFORE you emit
        the verdict;
     c) the deferral-authorizing ADR is in ACCEPTED state.
  4. Five anti-patterns mapped to verdicts:
     - "I think this works"          → NEEDS_HUMAN
     - "Tests pass on my mocked rig" → NEEDS_HUMAN (re-verify on canonical)
     - "Skipped the hard part"       → FAIL
     - "Need another turn"           → CONTINUE
     - "ADR conflict; needs human"   → NEEDS_HUMAN
  5. The LAST LINE of your output MUST match exactly:
     `VERDICT: PASS | PROXY_PASS | FAIL | NEEDS_HUMAN | CONTINUE | HUMAN_APPROVAL_REQUIRED`
  6. Immediately above the verdict line, post the verdict comment block:
     ```
     VERDICT: <one of the seven>
     Artifacts: <paths|urls>
     Summary: <1-3 sentences>
     Gate ref: <test-plan section or AC id>
     ```

  Begin.
```
